title: Nazareth's Nick Hinkle, Becahi's Nick Maff are medalists at D-11 Boys Golf Qualifying Tournament
text:
Nazareth's Nick Hinkle finished three strokes ahead of teammate Victor Tavares and Thomas Lakata of Central Catholic (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) By Karl Gilbert | lehighvalleylive.com View/Post Comments 
Nazareth Area High School junior Nick Hinkle and Bethlehem Catholic senior Nick Maff were the qualifying medalists Monday in the District 11 Boys Golf Qualifying Tournament at Locust Valley Golf Club in Upper SauconTownship. 
The low 26 scores in the AAA classification out of 51 players, the low 12 scores in the AA qualifier out of 23 players, and three exempt golfers advanced to the District 11 Golf Championships, to be played next Monday at Schuylkill Country Club in Orwigsburg. 
Hinkle shot 5-over-par 77 to lead the 51-player AAA qualifying field. Thomas Lakata, a junior at Allentown Central Catholic, and Nazareth junior Victor Tavares were second at 80. 
Maff shot a 3-over-par 75 to earn AA medalist honors by one stroke over Moravian Academy sophomore Bobby Beck , who shot 76. 
Notre Dame of East Stroudsburg freshman William Mirams was third at 78. 
Next Monday, Maff will seek to become only the second boy to win three District 11 golf titles. Jeff Billie of Emmaus won three straight from 1963-1965. Maff, who plans to continue his golf career at Monmouth University next year, won District 11 titles in 2012 and 2014. 
The cutoff score for AAA was 90, while the AA cutoff score was also 90. 
Three golfers were exempt from qualifying on Monday: Eastern Pennsylvania Conference champion Brian Whelan, a junior at Pocono Mountain East; Colonial League champion Colin McQueen, a senior at Moravian Academy; and Schuylkill League winner Tanner Cook of Blue Mountain.
